    "### TODO: Model Training\n",
    "\n",
    "\"#### Primary tasks (must-have)\\n\",\n",
     - [ ] **Reproducibility**: Set a global `RANDOM_STATE` (e.g., 42) for all models/CV to ensure results are repeatable.\n",
     - [ ] **Cross-Validation**: Implement `StratifiedKFold` (e.g., k=5) on the training set. Do not rely solely on a single validation split; this detects if your model is overfitting.\n",
     - [ ] **Leakage Prevention**: Ensure preprocessing (scaling, encoding) is wrapped inside an `sklearn.pipeline.Pipeline` so it runs *within* each CV fold.\n",
     - [ ] **Baseline Models (Model Selection)**: Train multiple estimators (RF, XGBoost, LightGBM, LogisticRegression) using the training split; compare valid metrics to select the best architecture.\n",
     - [ ] **Metrics**: Track **Precision, Recall, F1-Score (Macro & Weighted)**, and Confusion Matrix. Accuracy is often misleading for rare attacks.\n",
     - [ ] **Hyperparameter Search**: `RandomizedSearchCV` should emit both best params and performance deltas versus baseline.\n",
     - [ ] **[Supervised ML] Pipeline**: Lock down the final classifier as `Pipeline([('preprocessor', ColumnTransformer), ('clf', BestModel)])` (replacing TF-IDF text logic with Tabular OneHot/Scaling) and store tuned params.\n",
     - [ ] **[Unsupervised ML]**: Fit the Isolation Forest on the engineered numeric features (`Hour`, `Src_IP_LastOctet`, etc.) and persist the model.\n",
     - [ ] **Persist Artifacts**: Save the *final* selected model + preprocessing pipeline via `joblib.dump` for downstream inference.\n",
     - [ ] ** ADD Deep Learning Model for comparison

    "\n",
    "\n",
    " \"#### Secondary tasks (second essentials)\\n\",\n",
    "        - [ ] **Explainability**: Train a SHAP explainer on the final pipeline (using a background sample) and serialize it.\n",
